snippet.textDisplay:
Im not knocking Elana in anyway, but if they had put an experienced Hellcat or Demon driver in the Challenger it would've won everytime. Its like she said at the end, once the launch control turned off the tires spun in 3rd and 4th gear. Put a driver that is used to the way that the Hellcat handles and accelerates and it beats the GT500 and ZL1 everytime.

I kinda expected the GT500 to win though just because its like 600 lbs lighter and is only a few horsepower behind the Redeye. The ZL1 is more of a track car, it has really good downforce and its turning and handling are both great, but it doesn't have the acceleration.

snippet.textDisplay: I immediately discredited the video when I read "Redeye" and not "Demon". If the latter was in the race, the results would have certainly been different. The Demon was made specifically for the drag strip. Edmunds dropped the ball on this one. Wouldn't be surprised if this was a marketing ploy for the Shelby which is a great car. However, I'd be interested in how it would fare against the most powerful coupe Mopar has ever created.
